{"file_path": "/project/documentation/snapshot/docs/faq.md", "old_string": "An error can be suppressed using:

* EOL comments
* Block comments
* @Suppress annotations

=== "[:material-heart:](#) Suppress annotation"

    ```kotlin
    // Suppressing all rules for the entire file
    @file:Suppress("ktlint")

    // Suppress a single rule (with id 'rule-id', defined in rule set with id 'rule-set-id') from the annotated construct
    @Suppress("ktlint:rule-set-id:rule-id")
    class Foo {}

    // Suppress multiple rules for the annotated construct
    @Suppress("ktlint:standard:no-wildcard-imports", "ktlint:custom-rule-set-id:custom-rule-id")
    import foo.*

    // Suppress all rules for the annotated construct
    @Suppress("ktlint")
    import foo.*
    ```
=== "[:material-heart:](#) EOL comments"

    ```kotlin
    // Suppress a single rule for the commented line
    import foo.* // ktlint-disable standard_no-wildcard-imports

    // Suppress multiple rules for the commented line
    import foo.* // ktlint-disable standard_no-wildcard-imports standard_other-rule-id

    // Suppress all rules for the commented line
    import foo.* // ktlint-disable
    ```

=== "[:material-heart-off-outline:](#) Block comments"

    ```kotlin
    // Suppress a single rule for all code between the start and end tag
    /* ktlint-disable standard_no-wildcard-imports */
    import foo.*
    /* ktlint-disable standard_no-wildcard-imports */

    // Suppress multiple rules for all code between the start and end tag
    /* ktlint-disable standard_no-wildcard-imports standard_no-wildcard-imports */
    import foo.*
    /* ktlint-enable standard_no-wildcard-imports standard_no-wildcard-imports */

    // Suppress all rules for all code between the start and end tag
    /* ktlint-disable */
    import foo.*
    /* ktlint-enable */
    ```

!!! important
    When using the block comments, the `ktlint-enable` directive needs to specify the exact same rule-id's and in the same order as the `ktlint-disable` directive.

!!! warning
    From a consistency perspective seen, it might be best to **not** mix the (EOL/Block) comment style with the annotation style in the same project.", "new_string": "An error can be suppressed using `@Suppress` annotations:

```kotlin
// Suppressing all rules for the entire file
@file:Suppress("ktlint")

// Suppress a single rule (with id 'rule-id', defined in rule set with id 'rule-set-id') from the annotated construct
@Suppress("ktlint:rule-set-id:rule-id")
class Foo {}

// Suppress multiple rules for the annotated construct
@Suppress("ktlint:standard:no-wildcard-imports", "ktlint:custom-rule-set-id:custom-rule-id")
import foo.*

// Suppress all rules for the annotated construct
@Suppress("ktlint")
import foo.*
```

!!! warning
    The `ktlint-disable` and `ktlint-enable` directives in comments are no longer supported. Use `@Suppress` annotations instead."}

{"file_path": "/project/ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/DiscouragedCommentDirectiveRuleTest.kt", "content": "package com.pinterest.ktlint.ruleset.standard.rules

import com.pinterest.ktlint.test.KtLintAssertThat
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test

class DiscouragedCommentDirectiveRuleTest {
    private val ktLintAssertThat = KtLintAssertThat.assertThatRule { DiscouragedCommentDirectiveRule() }

    @Test
    fun `Given an EOL comment with ktlint-disable directive then report violation`() {
        val code =
            """
            val foo = "foo" // ktlint-disable
            """.trimIndent()
        ktLintAssertThat(code)
            .hasLintViolation(1, 17, "The ktlint-disable directive is no longer supported. Replace with @Suppress annotation.")
    }

    @Test
    fun `Given an EOL comment with ktlint-disable directive for specific rule then report violation`() {
        val code =
            """
            val foo = "foo" // ktlint-disable standard:some-rule
            """.trimIndent()
        ktLintAssertThat(code)
            .hasLintViolation(1, 17, "The ktlint-disable directive is no longer supported. Replace with @Suppress annotation.")
    }

    @Test
    fun `Given a block comment with ktlint-disable directive then report violation`() {
        val code =
            """
            /* ktlint-disable */
            val foo = "foo"
            /* ktlint-enable */
            """.trimIndent()
        ktLintAssertThat(code)
            .hasLintViolations(
                KtLintAssertThat.LintViolation(1, 1, "The ktlint-disable directive is no longer supported. Replace with @Suppress annotation."),
                KtLintAssertThat.LintViolation(3, 1, "The ktlint-enable directive is no longer supported. Remove this comment or replace with proper @Suppress annotation usage."),
            )
    }

    @Test
    fun `Given a block comment with ktlint-disable directive for specific rule then report violation`() {
        val code =
            """
            /* ktlint-disable standard:some-rule */
            val foo = "foo"
            /* ktlint-enable standard:some-rule */
            """.trimIndent()
        ktLintAssertThat(code)
            .hasLintViolations(
                KtLintAssertThat.LintViolation(1, 1, "The ktlint-disable directive is no longer supported. Replace with @Suppress annotation."),
                KtLintAssertThat.LintViolation(3, 1, "The ktlint-enable directive is no longer supported. Remove this comment or replace with proper @Suppress annotation usage."),
            )
    }

    @Test
    fun `Given normal comments without ktlint directives then do not report violations`() {
        val code =
            """
            // This is a normal comment
            val foo = "foo"
            /* This is a block comment */
            """.trimIndent()
        ktLintAssertThat(code).hasNoLintViolations()
    }

    @Test
    fun `Given a Suppress annotation then do not report violations`() {
        val code =
            """
            @Suppress("ktlint")
            val foo = "foo"
            """.trimIndent()
        ktLintAssertThat(code).hasNoLintViolations()
    }
}
"}

